Sentencas: The crystal chemistry, thermal expansion behavior, electrical conductivity, chemical compatibility, and electrochemical performance in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) of Nd1-xSrxCoO3-delta (0 less than or equal to x less than or equal to 0.5) perovskite oxides have been investigated.
Titulo: Characterization of Nd1-xSrxCoO3-δ (0≤x≤0.5) cathode materials for intermediate temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: The samples crystallize in an orthorhombic structure, and the lattice volume increases with increasing Sr content, x.
Titulo: Characterization of Nd1-xSrxCoO3-δ (0≤x≤0.5) cathode materials for intermediate temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: The thermal expansion coefficient decreases with x, reaches a minimum at x = 0.3, and then increases.
Titulo: Characterization of Nd1-xSrxCoO3-δ (0≤x≤0.5) cathode materials for intermediate temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity increases with x, and the system exhibits a semiconductor-to-metal transition at around x = 0.3.
Titulo: Characterization of Nd1-xSrxCoO3-δ (0≤x≤0.5) cathode materials for intermediate temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: The electrocatalytic activity and power density increase with increasing x, reaches a maximum around x = 0.4, and then decreases due to an interfacial reaction of the x = 0.5 sample with the electrolyte.
Titulo: Characterization of Nd1-xSrxCoO3-δ (0≤x≤0.5) cathode materials for intermediate temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: The x = 0.4 sample shows a maximum power density value of 0.24 W/cm(2) at 800degreesC in single cells fabricated with the La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O2.8 electrolyte and Ni-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 cermet anode.
Titulo: Characterization of Nd1-xSrxCoO3-δ (0≤x≤0.5) cathode materials for intermediate temperature SOFCs
